positions.description: I worked in team with Assistant Attorney Generals to provide legal service to citizens and assist in receiving payments for the Department of Health & Human Services from citizens. This job required me to aid in the closing of cases in a timely, independent manner. Finally, I provided friendly customer service when answering phone calls daily from citizens and I visited various court houses at the request of the several Assistant Attorney Generals and their secretaries.
positions.title: Student Assistant

positions.companyName: Center for Anti-Counterfeiting and Product Protection
positions.description: As an intern at Michigan State University, Center for Anti-Counterfeiting and Product Protection, I performed investigations of past counterfeit crimes in an independent and proficient manner. Additionally, I worked in team with other interns to develop a campaign to warn the elderly of possible counterfeit pharmaceuticals they could be purchasing as well as giving them a pathway to follow to resolve their predicament. Lastly, I removed counterfeit Michigan State University products off of websites selling them illegally.
